{"by":"nagonago","id":47747824,"kids":[47748553],"parent":47742200,"text":"When I got a Macbook many years ago, I was surprised how often little utility software like this cost money. I was just so used to the abundance of open source and freeware in the Windows&#x2F;Linux world.<p>No judgement either way, I get that developers want to be compensated for their time. I just always found the difference in culture curious. I guess it&#x27;s because if you&#x27;re willing to spend the extra premium for Apple products, you&#x27;re probably also willing to spend a little extra premium on the software too.","time":1776056906,"type":"comment"}